<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1158,1581]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
Diagnosis. Glp-1 same level as Ds-1. Ds-2 on membranous cuticle. PE with 1 dorsal seta. GA bipartite in female. Female with 6 Pgs and 4 Sgs. Tr I–IV with 1-1-1-1 setae; Bf I–IV with 2-2-1-1 setae; Tf I–IV with 5-4-2-2 setae, 2-0-0-0 Bp setae; Gn I–IV with 4-5-3-3 setae, 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Tb I–IV with 9-6-7-7 setae, 6-3-4-4 Bp setae; Ta I–IV with 3-3-3-3 dorsal setae, 1-1-0-0 Bp setae. Lc I with accessory process. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[1028,1132,1303,1329]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="29" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Idiosoma</taxonomicName>
length 
<quantity box="[1216,1343,1303,1329]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6674999999999995" metricValueMax="7.0358" metricValueMin="6.2992" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" unit="in" value="262.5" valueMax="277.0" valueMin="248.0">248–277 in</quantity>
female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1158,1581]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
Remarks. This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1977" box="[658,811,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Scaptognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauciporus">
<emphasis box="[658,811,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">S. pauciporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, distinguishable from the latter by the AE with strongly convex posterior margin and Tf II with 4 setae. Female is known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1158,1581]" box="[208,1059,1411,1437]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
Habitat. Littoral–Sublittoral zones: Medium to coarse sands at 
<quantity box="[912,983,1411,1437]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" unit="m" value="4.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="2.0">2–7 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1158,1581]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
Distribution. South Pacific Ocean: Yonge Reef, Boulder Reef (Great Barrier Reef), Lihou Reef (
<collectingRegion box="[1302,1436,1447,1473]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Queensland</collectingRegion>
Plateau) [
<collectingCountry box="[256,368,1482,1509]" name="Australia" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Australia</collectingCountry>
].
</paragraph>
